The number of confirmed COVID-19 cases in West Sussex so far as at 31 May is 42,228 (4,887.6 cases per 100,000 population). In the seven days to 26 May, there were 65 new confirmed cases (7.5 new cases per 100,000). In the seven days to 19 May, there were 53 new cases and so the new cases have risen by 23% (12 extra cases).
